    rationale: "Vulnerable plaques are characterized by: (1) a thin fibrous cap (<65 \u03bcm) that is susceptible to mechanical disruption; (2) a large necrotic lipid core rich in tissue factor; and (3) high macrophage density \u2014 macrophages secrete matrix metalloproteinases (MMPs) that degrade collagen in the fibrous cap, further thinning it. Stable plaques, by contrast, have a thick fibrous cap, smaller lipid core, and more smooth muscle cells producing collagen. Paradoxically, heavily calcified plaques may actually be more stable. The high macrophage burden is a feature of vulnerable, not stable, plaques.",
