    rationale: "In the Weber test, sound lateralizes to the affected ear in conductive hearing loss (because ambient noise masking is reduced in that ear, making bone-conducted sound relatively louder) and to the unaffected ear in sensorineural hearing loss (because the affected ear's cochlear/nerve function is impaired). Lateralization to the right means either: right conductive loss OR left sensorineural loss. Choice C reverses this logic. Choice A incorrectly interprets lateralization as indicating better function. Choice D is incorrect \u2014 normal hearing produces no lateralization (midline perception).",
